@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/barbie-margot-robbie@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/barbie-margot-robbie@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/barbie-margot-robbie@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/barbie-margot-robbie@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3428959" class="wp-caption-text"> Margot Robbie in &#39;Barbie&#39;. Credit: LANDMARK MEDIA / Alamy Stock Photo</figcaption></figure><p> Goldstein and Cripps added in a joint statement: “If there was one thing missing in this winning Barbie strategy, it was being able to put Greta&#39;s singular vision on premium IMAX screens over the uber-competitive summer corridor. That Barbie continues to draw packed audiences around the world heading into its sixth weekend in release speaks to the quality of the film and the excitement audiences have for the story. We are so pleased to give them a chance to see Barbie, whether for the first or fifth time, in such an experiential format as IMAX.”</p><p> In addition to becoming the highest-grossing film in the US this year, Barbie also has a chance to become the <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/barbie-overtakes-the-dark-knight-break-box-office-record-3484006">top performing movie of 2023 worldwide</a> , after <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/barbie-has-hit-1billion-at-the-global-box-office-3478941">hitting $1.2billion globally</a> . It currently sits behind <em>The Super Mario Bros. Movie, which amassed</em> $1.35billion.</p><p> Since it was released in July, the film has also become the highest-ever-grossing live-action movie directed by a woman.</p><p> “For all of us in the exhibition community, it&#39;s been exciting to watch an original film like Barbie become an unparalleled critical and commercial success this summer,” Richard Gelfond, CEO of IMAX Corporation, said in a statement. “We&#39;re thrilled to be partnering with Greta and her filmmaking team and our friends at Warner Bros. to deliver this special edition of Barbie with never-before-seen footage exclusively to IMAX audiences around the world.”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/barbie-looks-to-rival-oppenheimer-with-special-imax-screenings-3488132">&#39;Barbie&#39; looks to rival &#39;Oppenheimer&#39; with special IMAX screenings</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
